rComments: Really nice person. If she like your design style you will get high marks and really cares students' participation at classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Respected', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Best design prof Ive had. Isnt hung up on small details of the assignment and pushes to get good interesting work out of students. will let you break the assignment rules and wants to help with making good work for your portfolio

she has a good way of inspiring the class to think about design ideas as they pertain to everyday concepts. she is approachable and very nice. expects a lot of her students but is helpful with discussing ways to produce work on time

Her instruction was clear as well as her expectation for students' projects. The lectures were average but the desk critiques were rather useful. Easy to approach and fairly high class average in general. She would also defend students' projects during final reviews.

Flismy with grading expectations and what she likes/dislikes. Very nice person, but tough grader and unclear expectations. Expects you to do everything by hand which disadvantages students in later years.
